subtitleNullable: Let's Teach Neural Networks to Draw :)
descriptionNullable:
### Context

This dataset is planned for usage in the deep and transfer learning experiments. Mostly, for the process of generating new images based on the data.

### Content

Dataset creating is in progress, so the full description will be a little bit later.

The images are labeled by the file prefixes. Labels correspond to the following classification.

1) The first label (a manner): 

01=>pictogram; 02=>contour; 03=>sketch.

2) The second label (an object): 

001=>flower; 002=>bird; 003=>butterfly; 004=>tree; 005=>plane; 006=>crane;  007=>dog;

008=>horse; 009=>deer; 010=>truck; 011=>car; 012=>cat; 013=>frog; 014=>ship;

015=>fish; 016=>house.

### Inspiration

Is it possible for neural networks and other algorithms to be able to draw like a professional artist? At least, can they repeat a manner of human artists?
